This App helps Splunk user to perform the following operations
  * Get CIDR for given ipaddress and ipmask fields
----------------------------------------
Author: Jayanna Hallur
Version/Date: 1.0/12-08-2016
Ref : https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/6.5.1/Search/Customsearchcommandshape
Using this app: To get the IP CIDR for given ipaddress and ipmask fields in the Splunk search query
----------------------------------------

ABOUT
------
This app provides the following  custom splunk command 
    * ip2cidr - which returns IP CIDR for given 'ipaddress' & 'ipmask' fields.
    * iprange - which returns firstIP, LastIP & NetMask for given IP CIDR.

Syntax: 
...| ip2cidr ipaddress, ipmask |table ipaddress ipmask ipcidr
...| iprange ipcidr | table ipcidr, firstIP, lastIP, netMask

INSTALLATION
-------------
Install this app on Splunk search head or search head cluster. This app is invisible. The splunk command "ip2cidr" will be available globally.
